com.thomsonreuters.upa.examples.provider

Class MarketByOrderItems

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thomsonreuters.upa.examples.provider.MarketByOrderItems
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MarketByOrderCacheItems

    public class MarketByOrderItems
extends java.lang.Object
    This handles storage of all market by order items.

    Provides methods generation of market by order data, for managing the list, and a method for encoding a market by order message and payload.

        Encodes the market by order response. Returns success if encoding succeeds or failure if encoding fails.
        Parameters:
        channel - - The channel to send a market by order response to
        itemInfo - - The item information
        isSolicited - - The response is solicited if set
        msgBuf - - The message buffer to encode the market by order response into
        streamId - - The stream id of the market by order response
        isStreaming - - Flag for streaming or snapshot
        serviceId - - The service id of the market by order response
        dictionary - - The dictionary used for encoding
        error - - Error information in case of encoding failure
